5:
How about it, Façon? Are you almost
ready?
9: Sorry, just give me a little longer!
19:
Heed me, spirits of water. Unleash a
deluge upon my foes!
29:
Wow! That last attack was pretty
nifty.
33:
That it was... But it was all thanks to
my handy-dandy tank! Having you
around to distract enemies is great.
43:
No way! It's been AGES! We haven't
seen each other since... graduation, I
think?
46:
Oh... Hey.
Long time no see.
49:
Oh? Who's that cutie next to you?
Your boyfriend?
51:
N-no! He's just a fellow adventurer,
that's all.
54:
Really, now? What happened to all
that talk about going solo forever?
Hehe, I guess your massive book
would make that harder, wouldn't it?
61:
Classmates from my time at the
magic academy.
68:
Nice to meet you, Mr. Adventurer. I
bet traveling with Façon is pretty
tough, huh? Needs lots of looking
after, haha.
70:
For real. I mean, look at how huge
her book is! Must be hard to move
around with a massive thing like
that.
79: A shift! Everyone, be on guard!
88:
I can't see anything! Alk, this isn't
good. You'll have to fight it purely by
acting on instinct!
96:
This is getting out of hand! Now
there are more of them!
104:
Heed me, spirits of water. Spill forth,
and drown my enemies!
126: I-is it over? Did you get the monster?
130:
Yep. The coast is clear. Are you
unharmed?
134:
Quite the idea you had
there—turning the sand into mud
using water magic! Very innovative.
138:
Yeah... But I went and got everyone's
clothes all dirty.
141:
I can't just leave everyone all filthy
like this... Hold on a second.
145:
Heed me, spirits of water! Grant us
your cleansing powers and wash
away our squalor!
154:
What do you think? That was a
brand-new spell I came up with.
Made you all squeaky clean, didn't it?
164:
...Just THINK of the implications this
could have for the future of laundry!
168:
Is that really the first thing you think
of? Well, don't come running to me
every time you need your linens
washed. Doing that requires a LOT of
energy.
172:
My book may be massive and
heavy, but it certainly pulls through
for me in a pinch, huh?
175:
Wh-when did you learn to do
something like that?
177:
Er... Anyway, thanks for the help.
Bye.
187:
Oh, sorry about that. You guys ready
to go?
190:
Huh? Wouldn't it be a better idea to
rest a while first? You fired off a lot of
magic back there.
193:
Nah, I'm fine. I'll find time to rest
while monsters are beating away at
you, Alk.
197:
I'm not just here to be your meat
shield, you know!
202:
Don't worry, everything's going to be
fine. Let's go!
206:
You're certainly an assertive one,
you know that?
209:
Yeah, I guess. It's just there's a huge
world out there for me to learn
about!
212:
When I think of all of those new
discoveries waiting for me, I can't
help but get excited!
